26
00:05:33,855 --> 00:05:42,855
The tariff on exports and imports was set at a uniform rate of 5 percent.

27
00:05:49,855 --> 00:05:58,855
The Western powers had import tariffs ranging from 20 percent to 40 percent to protect their own industries.

28
00:05:58,855 --> 00:06:13,855
However, Japan was not allowed the right to change tariffs autonomously, so they could not stop the prolonged imports.

29
00:06:13,855 --> 00:06:20,855
Okubo Toshimichi

30
00:06:20,855 --> 00:06:30,855
Okubo Toshimichi, the leader of the government faced with the outflow of the nation's wealth, presented the idea of issuing rights certificates as a countermeasure.

31
00:06:30,855 --> 00:06:38,855
Even if agriculture and industry were encouraged, there was little to consume domestically.

32
00:06:50,432 --> 00:07:02,032
There is no one who is proficient in overseas trade, but it is most important to develop trade and expand reputation in the world.

33
00:07:02,032 --> 00:07:08,032
The base in French in Yokohama says the keyword "datsu-an-yu-o" (meaning to move away from troubles in Asia).

34
00:07:08,032 --> 00:07:19,032
What it meant was that Japan should not be distracted by troubles in Asia and should instead look out to the seven seas and leap forward in trade with the world.

35
00:07:19,032 --> 00:07:33,032
In other words, it was a way to theoretically justify the idea that Japan should become a trading nation.

36
00:07:33,032 --> 00:07:42,032
